title: National Capital Parks-East: Park Home
body: A Journey To Parks Beyond The Capital  Welcome to National Capital Parks-East. We invite you to journey to parks Beyond the Capital of Washington, D.C.Â  National Capital Parks-East is 13 park sites, parkways and statuary covering more than 8,000 acres of historic, cultural, and recreational parklands from Capitol Hill to the nearby Maryland suburbs              Find a Park   National Capital Parks-East manages a diverse set of parks in Maryland and Washington, D.C.            Volunteer   Our parks depend on you to be their best!        Management   National Capital Parks-East is an administrative unit of the National Park Service. It manages parks in Maryland and Washington, D.C.
